expenditure per person","The average life expectancy in years","The sum of years of life lost and years lived with disability","The number of deaths per 100,000 population"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe sum of years of life lost and years lived with disability\u003C/strong\u003E accurately describes DALYs. This metric combines premature mortality (years of life lost) with morbidity (years lived with disability) to provide a comprehensive measure of disease burden.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA measure of mortality rates only\u003C/strong\u003E fails to capture the impact of non-fatal health conditions that cause disability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe total healthcare expenditure per person\u003C/strong\u003E measures economic costs rather than health impact.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe average life expectancy in years\u003C/strong\u003E indicates expected lifespan but does not account for quality of life or disability.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThe number of deaths per 100,000 population\u003C/strong\u003E only captures mortality and ignores disability burden.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDALYs enable comparison of disease burden across different populations and health conditions by capturing both fatal and non-fatal outcomes in a single measure. One DALY represents the loss of one year of healthy life.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Disability-adjusted life years (DALYs) combine years of life lost due to premature death and years lived with disability.","One DALY represents the loss of one year of healthy life.","DALYs are used to measure disease burden and compare health outcomes across populations."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56252"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17431"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56252","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56252"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T14:02:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T14:02:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10121"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70786"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5326","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/5326"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf0f","name":"Public Health","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2